Author: Primas_Jo
Title: [ANN] Primas (PST) - Restoring Health to the Internet
Body: As with any tech-product company, revenue comes from size and adoption.  When we look at unicorns such as airbnb, uber, ofo, tiktok etc. We see that the ability to make a very, very small amount can actually accumulate to a great deal with enough volume. That being said, as the Primas DApp is decentralised, there is no official way for the Primas team to generate revenue from it.  Our revenue stems from other products (we currently have 6 in various stages of development) including a mixture of B2C, B2B and P2P models of SaaS, open sourced "gifts" to the technical world and of course our example of how this technology all comes together - the Primas DApp.

Author: Primas_Jo
Title: [ANN] Primas (PST) - Restoring Health to the Internet
Body: We see the vision of the man credited with inventing the Internet - Tim Berners Lee - as he talks about how devastated he is at the current state of the internet https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2018/07/the-man-who-created-the-world-wide-web-has-some-regrets  He said himself, Quote The Web as I envisaged it, we have not seen it yet. The future is still so much bigger than the past.    We believe the single biggest underlying problem with the Internet is the 'traffic economy', which is a result of advertising money and which leads to an impenetrable sea of clickbait, fake news, SEO manipulation by large centralised platforms and plagiarism. Good content is lost in this sea and the system perpetuates itself as traffic = money = power = traffic.  We believe above all else, quality should be the single greatest factor in what information is spread around the Internet and see it as our mission, armed with our technology, to take part in this movement.

Author: Primas_Jo
Title: [ANN] Primas (PST) - Restoring Health to the Internet
Body: Many projects in this space rely on viral marketing, paid shills and building hype through giveaways.  At Primas, we believe quality above all else should determine value. Our mission is to Restore Health to the Internet and in doing so we must walk the walk. As our project has reached the stage where we have something tangible to present (even if it’s not perfect), we’re ready to really start promoting ourselves and growing our community.  The reason for no bitcointalk thread until now is because we refuse to promise the world without anything to show for it.  Primas is different to other projects and I’m sure you’ll see us popping up more and more
